<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Signal to the Metric that is computed from it (specified level). For the actual-level counterpart see evaluatedBy."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "read by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a Metric to the Signal it is computed from (specified level). For the actual-level counterpart see evaluatesProperty."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#readsFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "reads from"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureMode> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a Failure Mode to the Metric(s) used for its detection or characterization. Establishes which quantitative assessments are diagnostic indicators."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#refersToMetric> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "refers to metric"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#rest
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepList> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepList> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Points to the remainder of the ordered step list. Together with mqto:first, implements a linked-list pattern terminated at mqto:nil."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#rest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "rest"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Specifies which data property of mqto:Result instances a Metric reads to obtain its input value. Each Metric selects exactly one property from Result instances that may carry multiple measured values."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "result property"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "Meta-level construct: an object property whose value is itself a property. Falls outside normal OWL type-system validation but provides a simple, declarative way to parameterise Metrics without requiring SPARQL property-path strings or SHACL infrastructure."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#resultProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "A PLC cycle produces one Result with three data properties:\n  ex:Result_Shot042  ex:temperature  718.3 ;\n                     ex:pressure     980.0 ;\n                     ex:cycleTime     24.7 .\n\nTwo Metrics select different properties from the same Result:\n  ex:TemperatureMetric  mqto:resultProperty  ex:temperature .\n  ex:PressureMetric     mqto:resultProperty  ex:pressure .\n\nAt query time: SELECT ?value WHERE { ?metric mqto:resultProperty ?prop . ?result ?prop ?value . }"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Signal> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureSourceCategory> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Associates a Signal with the FailureSourceCategory that provides it. Establishes the source of measurement or control data channels."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#signalProvidedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "signal provided by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a FailureOccurrence to a CountermeasureExecution that was recommended in response. Distinct from mitigatedOccurrence (which records actual resolution)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggested> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "suggested"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a CountermeasureExecution to the FailureOccurrence that triggered its recommendation. Distinct from mitigatedByExecution (which records actual resolution)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#suggestedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "suggested by"@en .
