# https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Human-readable explanation of why a CountermeasureStepExecution or CountermeasureExecution was aborted before completion."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedReason> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "aborted reason"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a CountermeasureStepExecution or CountermeasureExecution was aborted before normal completion."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#abortedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "aborted time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The calculation method applied by a Metric to compute its value from observations. Describes the algorithm or statistical function used to aggregate data."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "assessment method"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentMethod> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "average, maximum, standard deviation, trend slope"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Boolean pass/fail decision from threshold comparison. True indicates a threshold violation (failure detected), false indicates normal operation within bounds."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#assessmentValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "assessment value"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a MetricAssessment was computed. Marks the moment the metric calculation and threshold comparison were evaluated."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "calculated time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#MetricAssessment> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The computed numeric value of a MetricAssessment, preserving the quantitative result before threshold comparison."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "calculated value"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#calculatedValue> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "Unit of measurement is inherited from the implemented Metric specification."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureStepExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when a CountermeasureStepExecution was successfully completed. If a step is aborted, use abortedTime instead."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#completionTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "completion time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when an activity or time-bound entity concluded. General-purpose temporal property applicable to execution contexts."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#endTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "end time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A unique identifier for an entity. Enables correlation between ontology instances and external systems."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "identifier"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "Conceptually aligned with dcterms:identifier but declared independently because OWL 2 DL does not permit a datatype property to be a subproperty of an annotation property."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#identifier> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "machine serial number, material batch code, signal name, process ID"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The number of production items over which a Metric aggregates observations. Complements timeWindowSize for item-count-based windows."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "item window size"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#itemWindowSize> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "last 10 shots, last 5 batches"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#Metric> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The minimum acceptable threshold value for a Metric. Values below the lowerBound indicate a threshold violation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "lower bound"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#lowerBound> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "Stored as dimensionless xsd:double; unit of measurement determined by the Metric's associated Signal."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#FailureOccurrence> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when this failure occurrence actually happened in the physical world. Essential for failure frequency analysis and temporal correlation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#occurrenceTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "occurrence time"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#score
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/mqto#CountermeasureExecution> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A numeric score or confidence value assigned to a CountermeasureExecution recommendation. Used by diagnostic systems to rank countermeasure suggestions."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "score"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#score> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "The interpretation and scale of scores is application-specific."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#startTime> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The timestamp when an activity or time-bound entity began. General-purpose temporal property applicable to execution contexts."@en .
