<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An observable property of a FailureSource that can be measured via Observations. Implements a Signal specification."@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <https://w3id.org/mqto/1.0> .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Observable Property"@en .
<https://w3id.org/mqto#ObservableProperty> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "Subclassing both sosa:ObservableProperty (an abstract quality type) and lis:Actual (via mqto:Property) reflects that each individual is a concrete instance tied to a particular item, not a reusable abstract type. This parallels how sosa:ObservableProperty instances are used in practice (e.g. 'the temperature of this specific machine part')."@en .
